headline: MetLife (MET): Assessing Valuation After Recent Share Price Weakness
summary: MetLife (MET) shares finished slightly higher today, ending at $76.15, after a stretch of mixed returns over the past month. Investors appear to be weighing valuation and recent business momentum as they consider the stock's outlook. See our latest analysis for MetLife. MetLife’s recent dip in share price, down 7.2% over the past month, builds on a broader pattern with the stock delivering a -3.3% total shareholder return for the past year.
